hands_on_practices.solution:
1. 归一化常数 $C$ 由下式给出
$$\int_0^{\pi/2}C\,\sin^p\theta\cos^q\theta\,d\theta=1
\quad\Longrightarrow\quad
C=\frac1{\int_0^{\pi/2}\sin^p\theta\cos^q\theta\,d\theta}
=\frac2{B\bigl(\tfrac{p+1}2,\tfrac{q+1}2\bigr)}.$$
2. 期望值
$$\langle\sec^2\theta\rangle
=\int_0^{\pi/2}\sec^2\theta\,f(\theta)\,d\theta
=C\int_0^{\pi/2}\sin^p\theta\,\cos^{q-2}\theta\,d\theta
=\frac{2}{B\bigl(\tfrac{p+1}2,\tfrac{q+1}2\bigr)}
\cdot\frac12\,B\bigl(\tfrac{p+1}2,\tfrac{q-1}2\bigr).$$
3. 因此
$$\langle\sec^2\theta\rangle
=\frac{B\bigl(\tfrac{p+1}2,\tfrac{q-1}2\bigr)}
     {B\bigl(\tfrac{p+1}2,\tfrac{q+1}2\bigr)}
=\frac{\Gamma\bigl(\tfrac{q-1}2\bigr)\,\Gamma\bigl(\tfrac{p+q}2+1\bigr)}
     {\Gamma\bigl(\tfrac{q+1}2\bigr)\,\Gamma\bigl(\tfrac{p+q}2\bigr)}
=\frac{\tfrac{p+q}2}{\tfrac{q-1}2}
=\frac{p+q}{q-1}.$$
